data.title: "Hairspray" Teased At ShoWest
data.meta_description: Stars, Including John Travolta, Turn Out To Promote Summer Movie Musical
data.text:
Nicole Blonsky is kissed by John Travolta as they pose for photographers during ShoWest, the official convention of the National Association of Theatre Owners, March 14, 2007, in Las Vegas. They co-star in "Hairspray" as mother and daughter Edna and Tracy Turnblad. "Hairspray" is set for release in the U.S. on July 20, 2007.

Nicole Blonsky and John Travolta, who play daughter and mother in the new movie version of "Hairspray," appear together at ShoWest on March 14, 2007, in Las Vegas.

John Travolta escorts his movie daughter, Nicole Blonsky, to an event to promote their movie, "Hairspray," during ShoWest, the official convention of the National Association of Theatre Owners on March 14, 2007, in Las Vegas.

John Travolta and Nicole Blonsky, who play mother and daughter Edna and Tracy Turnblad in the new film version of "Hairspray," pose for photos at the ShoWest convention in Las Vegas on March 14, 2007.

Queen Latifah, left, who plays Motormouth Maybelle in "Hairspray," and Michelle Pfeiffer, who plays Velma von Tussel, joke around during ShoWest, the official convention of the National Association of Theatre Owners on March 14, 2007, in Las Vegas.

Queen Latifah poses for photographers at ShoWest on March 14, 2007, in Las Vegas. She co-stars in a new movie version of "Hairspray" as Motormouth Maybelle.

Actress Michelle Pfeiffer, who plays Velma von Tussel in the new version of the film "Hairspray," poses for photos at the ShoWest convention in Las Vegas on March 14, 2007.

Actress Michelle Pfeiffer attends ShoWest in Las Vegas on March 14, 2007, in support of the new movie version of "Hairspray," to be released in the U.S. on July 20, 2007.

Brittany Snow plays Amber von Tussel in the new movie version of "Hairspray." Here, she poses for photographers at ShoWest, the official convention of the National Association of Theatre Owners, on March 14, 2007, in Las Vegas.

Actor Christopher Walken plays Wilbur Turnblad, the husband of John Travolta's character, in the new movie version of "Hairspray." Here, he appears at ShoWest on March 14, 2007.

Actor Zac Efron, who plays Link Larkin in "Hairspray," poses for photographers at ShoWest in Las Vegas on March 14, 2007.

Actor Zac Efron, who plays love interest Link Larkin in the new film "Hairspray," poses for photos at the ShoWest convention in Las Vegas on March 14, 2007.

Actor Elijah Kelley, who plays Seaweed in the new movie version of "Hairspray," poses for photographers during ShoWest, the official convention of the National Association of Theatre Owners, on March 14, 2007, in Las Vegas.

Actress Allison Janney, who plays Prudy Pingleton, comes out to support the new movie version of "Hairspray" during ShoWest, the official convention of the National Association of Theatre Owners, on March 14, 2007, in Las Vegas.

Allison Janney, who plays Prudy Pingleton in the movie "Hairspray," poses for a photo during ShoWest, the official convention of the National Association of Theatre Owners, on March 14, 2007, in Las Vegas.

Actress Nicole Blonsky has the lead role of Tracy Turnblad in the new movie version of "Hairspray," to be released in the U.S. on July 20, 2007. Here, she poses at ShoWest, the official convention of the National Association of Theatre Owners, on March 14, 2007, in Las Vegas.

Actor John Travolta, who plays Edna Turnblad in the new film version of "Hairspray," poses for photos at the ShoWest convention in Las Vegas on March 14, 2007.

Director Adam Shankman turns out for the movie "Hairspray" at Paris Las Vegas during ShoWest, the official convention of the National Association of Theatre Owners, on March 14, 2007, in Las Vegas.
